n%3Cli%3EI've%20often%20been%20told%20to%20%26quot%3Blive%20on%20less%20than%20you%20make%26quot%3B%20if%20you%20want%20to%20be%20wealthy%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20buy%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20always%20stick%20to%20a%20budget%20and%20I'm%20careful%20with%20my%20money%2C%20but%20this%20advice%20doesn't%20always%20make%20sense.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20I%20was%20building%20my%20business%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20invest%20money%20I%20didn't%20have%20yet%20to%20get%20things%20off%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20spent%20the%20past%20few%20years%20working%20overtime%20to%20fix%20up%20my%20finances%20after%20making%20many%20mistakes%20in%20my%2020s%2C%20from%20not%20saving%20money%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20having%20bad%20spending%20habits.%20It's%20almost%20become%20an%20obsession%20of%20mine%20to%20seek%20out%20tactics%2C%20advice%2C%20and%20strategies%20that%20can%20help%20me%20grow%20my%20net%20worth%20and%20streamline%20how%20I%20manage%20my%20finances%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20consume%20financial%20advice%20and%20seek%20help%20from%20financial%20experts%2C%20there's%20one%20tip%20I%20hear%20quite%20often%3A%20Always%20live%20on%20less%20than%20you%20make.%20This%20means%20that%20you%20should%20spend%20less%20than%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20you%20make%20each%20month%20from%20your%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20a%20big%20advocate%20for%20sticking%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20taking%20on%20unnecessary%20debt%2C%20and%20being%20in%20control%20of%20your%20finances%20so%20you%20can%20see%20the%20impact%20your%20money%20decisions%20have%20on%20your%20overall%20portfolio%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20reasons%20I%20don't%20like%20the%20advice%20that%20you%20should%20always%20live%20on%20less%20than%20you%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20There%20are%20times%20when%20it's%20important%20to%20invest%20in%20yourself%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20laid%20off%20from%20my%20full-time%20job%20in%202015%2C%20I%20learned%20a%20money%20lesson%20I%20was%20too%20stubborn%20to%20understand%20before%3A%20Sometimes%2C%20you%20have%20to%20invest%20in%20yourself%20so%20you%20can%20make%20more%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20layoff%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20go%20into%20business%20for%20myself%2C%20but%20there%20was%20a%20period%20when%20I%20wasn't%20earning%20any%20income.%20However%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20had%20to%20invest%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20in%20courses%2C%20freelance%20help%2C%20and%20digital%20tools%20so%20I%20could%20go%20off%20and%20become%20a%20solopreneur.%20I%20pulled%20from%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20put%20some%20of%20the%20charges%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-zero-interest-credit-cards%5C%22%3E0%25%20interest%20credit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20spending%20was%20calculated%20and%20considered%2C%20and%20even%20though%20it%20came%20with%20risks%20(there%20was%20no%20guarantee%20this%20route%20as%20a%20solopreneur%20would%20work%20or%20be%20profitable)%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20give%20it%20a%20try.%20I%20took%20all%20the%20measures%20necessary%20to%20be%20strategic%20about%20my%20decisions%20(competitor%20research%2C%20audience%20testing%2C%20and%20writing%20out%20a%20business%20plan).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20stuck%20with%20the%20mantra%20of%20living%20below%20my%20means%2C%20I%20would%20have%20put%20off%20investing%20in%20these%20tools%20until%20I%20took%20a%20part-time%20or%20full-time%20job%20that%20brought%20in%20income%20to%20make%20this%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20spent%20more%20than%20I%20could%20afford%20and%20leveraged%20those%20costs%20to%20help%20me%20start%20a%20business.%20Within%20three%20months%2C%20my%20business%20was%20profitable%2C%20and%20it%20helped%20me%20pay%20off%20the%20credit%20card%20and%20replenish%20my%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20It%20limits%20people%20to%20not%20go%20after%20other%20streams%20of%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20times%20in%20my%20life%20when%20I've%20wanted%20to%20upgrade%20my%20lifestyle%2C%20like%20when%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20a%20roommate%20anymore%20or%20when%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20to%20take%20a%20vacation%20or%20two%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20just%20told%20myself%20that%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20these%20things%20because%20I%20wasn't%20earning%20enough%2C%20then%20I'd%20be%20stuck%20with%20a%20limited%20mindset%20that%20didn't%20allow%20my%20finances%20and%20my%20goals%20to%20see%20any%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%C2%A0my%20urge%20to%20live%20above%20my%20means%20has%20made%20me%20more%20passionate%20about%20exploring%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpassive-income-streams-millionaires-retirement-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassive%20income%20streams%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20new%20business%20opportunities%2C%20and%20ways%20to%20increase%20growth%20within%20my%20current%20side%20hustles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20who%20is%20cautious%20about%20how%20they%20spend%20their%20cash%2C%20when%20I%20want%20to%20upgrade%20my%20lifestyle%2C%20I%20make%20sure%20I%20have%20the%20money%20first.%20But%20rather%20than%20finding%20ways%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20other%20spending%20to%20afford%20a%20vacation%20or%20the%20rental%20cost%20of%20a%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20on%20my%20current%20salary%2C%20I%20think%20about%20ways%20to%20earn%20more%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20It's%20advice%20that%20doesn't%20apply%20to%20every%20moment%20of%20your%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20big%20proponent%20of%20sticking%20to%20a%20budget%2C%20but%20there%20are%20still%20one-off%20situations%20where%20I%20decide%20to%20splurge%20and%20live%20above%20my%20means%20temporarily.%20That%20might%20include%20incurring%20the%20costs%20of%20a%20wedding%2C%20paying%20for%20an%20occasional%20trip%2C%20investing%20in%20myself%2C%20or%20upgrading%20an%20item%20like%20a%20computer%20or%20bed%20that%20is%20a%20big%20part%20of%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20before%20taking%20on%20these%20costs%20that%20I%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20with%20cash%2C%20I%20make%20a%20plan%20for%20how%20I'm%20going%20to%20pay%20for%20these%20items%20without%20taking%20on%20tremendous%20debt.%20That%20might%20mean%20taking%20on%20an%20extra%20side%20hustle%2C%20opening%20a%200%25%20APR%20credit%20card%2C%20or%20pulling%20from%20my%20savings.%20I%20always%20make%20a%20plan%20to%20cover%20my%20excess%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20understand%20that%20my%20perspective%20on%20this%20advice%20is%20unusual%2C%20but%20I%20know%20that%20with%20the%20help%20of%20professionals%20and%20my%20own%20risk%20analysis%2C%20following%20this%20path%20has%20only%20helped%20me%20expand%20my%20lifestyle%20and%20my%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20June%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-believe-advice-live-on-less-than-you-make-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733016242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f98533a0c60aa00190d48da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-believe-advice-live-on-less-than-you-make-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Entrepreneur%20Jen%20Glantz%20says%20she%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20get%20her%20