nces%2C%20or%20friends.%20You%20come%20to%20find%20out%20after%20getting%20married%20is%20that%20people%2C%20even%20strangers%2C%20tend%20to%20ask%20about%20that%20kind%20of%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20bolder%20moments%2C%20I%20tended%20to%20fall%20back%20on%20things%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjd-vance-climate-change-children-families-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20climate%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20impending%20collapse%20of%20civilization%20as%20reasons%20for%20why%20I%20did%20not%20want%20to%20bring%20a%20child%20into%20this%20world.%20The%20rationale%20seemed%20unassailable.%20Perhaps%2C%20I%20reasoned%2C%20if%20the%20world%20were%20somehow%20different%20%E2%80%94%20somehow%20better%2C%20more%20equitable%2C%20more%20of%20a%20sure%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20then%20I%2C%20too%2C%20would%20feel%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229f97fa03-f32d-429f-95fc-ef7354c251f3%5C%22%3EWe%20talked%20about%20adoption%20in%20our%2030s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20our%2020s%20came%20to%20a%20close%20and%20we%20entered%20the%20era%20of%20our%2030s%2C%20it%20became%20a%20settled%20matter%20of%20fact%20that%20there%20would%20be%20no%20biological%20children%20in%20our%20future.%20Even%20so%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20adoption%20occasionally%20popped%20up.%20In%20theory%2C%20it%20removed%20the%20physical%20risk%20of%20either%20having%20to%20carry%20or%20give%20birth%20to%20a%20child%2C%20two%20things%20that%20understandably%20terrified%20my%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20even%20reasoned%20that%20adopting%20a%20kid%20would%20allow%20us%20to%20entirely%20skip%20the%20sleepless%20newborn%20stage%20and%20the%20terrible%20twos%2C%20which%20our%20friends%20with%20kids%20had%20recounted%20with%20something%20resembling%20shellshock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20our%20conversations%20about%20adoption%20were%20never%20really%20about%20wanting%20children.%20Instead%2C%20I%20think%20they%20were%20echoes%20of%20the%20same%20conversations%20we'd%20been%20having%20since%20we%20first%20met%2C%20in%20which%20we%20attempted%20to%20reconcile%20the%20possibility%20of%20our%20future%20selves%20against%20who%20we%20were%20and%20who%20we%20had%20become%20and%2C%20perhaps%2C%20who%20we%20had%20always%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20any%20meaningful%20distinction%20to%20be%20found%20between%20having%20kids%20and%20being%20a%20parent%2C%20it%20is%20perhaps%20wholly%20semantic.%20Whereas%20having%20kids%20connotes%20the%20act%20of%20giving%20birth%20and%20perhaps%20raising%20children%20as%20some%20sort%20of%20finite%20endeavor%20with%20a%20finish%20line%20stretched%20across%20the%20path%20into%20adulthood%2C%20being%20a%20parent%20emphasizes%20that%20the%20commitment%20is%20a%20lifelong%20one.%20It's%20not%20that%20I'm%20especially%20afraid%2C%20though%20that%20is%20part%20of%20it%3B%20it%20has%20more%20to%20do%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20time%20is%20limited%20and%20precious%2C%20and%20I%20would%20like%20to%20spend%20mine%20another%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20realization%20that%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20a%20parent%20has%20been%20clarifying%2C%20if%20only%20because%20figuring%20out%20what%20we%20don't%20want%20often%20sharpens%20our%20earnest%20desires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20a%20parent%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20be%20a%20supportive%20husband.%20I%20want%20to%20spend%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life%20with%20my%20wife.%20I%20want%20us%20to%20grow%20old%20together.%20I%20want%20us%20to%20feel%20in%20the%20everyday%20rhythms%20of%20our%20relationship%20the%20evidence%20of%20the%20love%20that%20brought%20us%20together%20and%20made%20visible%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20life%20we%20now%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwe-dont-want-kids-but-want-to-be-together-forever-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732989181000%2C%22visu